The article is a memorandum addressed to the Secretary of State regarding the delegation of authority under Section 506(a)(1) and Section 614(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. President Joseph R. Biden Jr. delegates the following authorities to the Secretary of State:

1. The authority to direct the drawdown of up to $800 million in defense articles and services from the Department of Defense, as well as military education and training, for providing assistance to Ukraine. The Secretary of State is also responsible for making the necessary determinations required under Section 506(a)(1) to carry out this drawdown.

2. The authority to determine whether it is in the security interests of the United States to provide up to $122 million in assistance to Ukraine, without being bound by any provision of law covered under Section 614(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act.

The memorandum concludes by authorizing the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.